<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><a href="" title="Show information"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information"></a><span style="color: #D40019;">Assignment Example #1:</span> Home Loans Product Analytics and Competitive Intelligence</p></h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Group Description</h3>
<p class="bac">Home Loans Product Analytics supports the business by providing proactive analysis of the product, trends, competitive landscape and other key business needs. This team partners with Market Intelligence and Marketing Analytics. Users of this information include executive management, product managers and the innovation team.</p>
<h3 class="bac">Responsibilities:</h3>
<p class="bac">This candidate will help to build out and automate our competitive intelligence routines and rigor. We will define our product &#39;niche" to assure it syncs up with, but not overlaps with our key partners. Additionally, we will work with our "internal customers" to see how we can enhance the current reports and move our findings to a more proactive commentary and analysis role. This position will work directly with the team leader and in partnership with the current associate on the team who is responsible for competitive intelligence.</p>
</div></div>

<div class="expand">
<h2 class="bac"><a href="" title="Show information"><img class="popen" src="../images/clear.gif" alt="Show information" title="Show information"></a><span style="color: #D40019;">Assignment Example #2:</span> Origination Credit Policy Group</h2>
<div>
<h3 class="bac">Group Description</h3>
<p class="bac nobr">Origination Credit Policy, an integral part of the Credit Origination Strategies group, helps fulfill the corporate mission of managing credit risk while offering world-class first mortgage products that benefit both the customer and Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America. Origination Credit Policy team members are loan program and policy experts in first mortgage credit policy. The organization is responsible for the following:</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Ongoing development and policy change management of enterprise-wide credit origination policies and credit risk strategies for GSE standard and negotiated programs; GSE Affordable programs; Mortgage Insurance; FHA policy; VA policy; Mortgage Insurance policy and vendors; Non-conforming mortgage programs and policy; Balance Sheet mortgage programs and policies; and Automated Underwriting Systems;</li>
	<li>Assess the impact of policy and product changes, then implement policy change using the Product Change process;</li>
	<li>Alignment and ongoing management of credit policy for the Fannie Mae and Freddie Mac master agreements;</li>
	<li>Policy oversight, including cross reporting on product performance, quality-control results, and repurchase volume;</li>
	<li>Ongoing assessment and improvement of mortgage loan manufacturing quality; and</li>
	<li>Provide information support as credit policy subject-matter experts to all levels of Bank management.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="bac">Responsibilities:</h3>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>The candidate will assist in two capacities for two teams: (1) Investor Relations and Governance, and (2) Loan Quality Initiative.</li>
	<li>Leverage Six Sigma knowledge tools to recommend innovative solutions for information management and workflow.</li>
	<li>Create and implement practices and processes that will drive accountability to comply with governance policies.</li>
	<li>Compile audit results and create analytical summaries (root cause analysis and performance trends).</li>
</ul>
</div></div>

